	<main>
		<img width="2500" height="1201" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-21st-century-sturgeon.jpg" class="singlepostthumb wp-post-image" alt="caviar on a cracker" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-21st-century-sturgeon.jpg 2500w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-21st-century-sturgeon-520x250.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-21st-century-sturgeon-1200x576.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-21st-century-sturgeon-768x369.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-21st-century-sturgeon-1536x738.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-21st-century-sturgeon-2048x984.jpg 2048w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-21st-century-sturgeon-900x432.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /><div class="post-thumbnail-caption">Synonymous with wealth and status, caviar has entered the 21st century to the detriment of the fish that provides the bounty: sturgeon. The Picture Pantry Ltd./Alamy Stock Photo</div>
			<article class="main container col4">
								<header class="maincol">
										<h1 class="pagetitle">Caviar Pizzas, New Money, and the Death of an Ancient Fish</h1>
										<h2 class="dek singlepagecontainer">Fancy fish eggs have become the latest luxury good to go viral on social media, raising questions about the future of sturgeon.</h2>
										<section class="singlebyline singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Authored by</h3>
						by  
										<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/paul-greenberg/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_top" >Paul Greenberg</a>								<br/>
												</section>
					 
					<aside class="singlebydatewords singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Wordcount</h3>
						December 10, 2024 | 4,700 words, about 24 minutes
					</aside>

					
				</header>

				
